===Etymology 1===
The sense of "safeguard" comes from {{L.}} ''[[Palladium]]'' (the image of [[Pallas]] that protected [[Troy]]), from {{Gr.}} ''[[Παλλάδιον]]'', from ''[[Πάλλας]]'', an alternative name for [[Athena]].

===Etymology 2===
The element was named after [[w:Pallas|Pallas]], an [[asteroid]] that had been discovered two years before the element.

====Noun====
'''palladium''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''palladia''' ''or'' '''palladium''')
{{wikipedia}}

# {{countable}} a safeguard (''from a statue of Athena that was believed to safeguard the ancient city of Troy'').
# {{uncountable}} a metallic chemical element (''symbol'' Pd) with an [[atomic number]] of 46.

